description.2: THE SENTRY STRIKES! Mar-Vell clashes with one of the greatest terrors from his Kree homeworld! Can even the Human Torch help Mar-Vell survive this battle?
description.3: Daredevil is overwhelmed by two pressing cases -- a mad bomber on the loose, and an at-risk runaway teen!
description.7: PANTHER'S RAGE CONCLUSION: Black Panther is challenged by a new villain… Wind Eagle!
description.13: Sersi and Margot have been captured by the Deviants and are headed to their undersea kingdom of Lemuria!! Eternals Makkari and Thena come to earth to help defend New York from the Deviant attack, but are they too little, too late?
description.14: Tragedy clouds the love between Hulk and Jarella. Will Doctor Strange use his mystic might to prevent Jarella's certain death?
description.15: Look who's back deadlier than ever! It's the mysterious Melter, the one foe who can destroy Shell Head's armor, and if Iron Man falls no one can stand against him! At least no one made of metal...
description.16: Just as James-Michael is starting to come to terms with his strange new life, he makes another shocking discovery - he can read people's thoughts!
description.17: Thor and Ulik make an uneasy alliance and Thor will have to make a costly decision - save the trolls or learn more about where to find Odin.
description.18: It's Silver Surfer, wielder of the Power Cosmic, versus Dracula, Lord of the Vampires! Who will triumph?
description.19: Warlock and Gamora wander the spaceways in search of their destinies...
description.20: The Impossible Man wreaks havoc in the Marvel Comics office! Stan "The Man" Lee and Jack Kirby guest-star. Will the Impossible Man land his own ongoing series?
description.27: Captain America reflects on an earlier battle with Reaper...
description.28: After a stormy argument, Beverly finally has had enough of Howard's stubbornness and splits! And when Howard goes for a stroll and is discovered by religious extremists who believe him to be a demon, things go from bad to worse.
description.34: Punisher tracks down Spider-Man and Nightcrawler, believing that one of the heroes framed him as the Coney Island sniper. After an impressive battle, Punisher and Spider-Man agree to team-up to uncover the truth behind the shootings. Will the true identity of the gunman be revealed?
description.35: The Scarlet Witch is attacked by the Living Laser, after she seeks a magical artifact at the Brant Corporation. But what does Wanda want with the Serpent Crown? And why is the Laser so keen on having the crown for himself?
description.36: Cap and Falcon take on Brother Inquisitor, Brother Wonderful, and the Night People on in another dimension!
description.41: Karen Page makes her long-awaited return in a calamitous crossover with Ghost Rider!
description.42: The Spirit of Vengeance is joined by the Man Without Fear to save Karen Page from the fatal grasp of Death’s Head! New ground is broken in Johnny and Roxanne’s relationship.
description.43: The Hulk's love, Jarella, has been captured and quarantined! And you think you've seen the Hulk mad before…
description.47: The Thing travels from 1976 to 1942, and fights super-powered Nazis alongside the Liberty Legion to reclaim the Canister of Vibranium!
description.52: The Thing realizes that the Nazis may still be able to win WWII with their half of the Canister of Vibranium!
description.53: During his Darkmoor battle, Brian Braddock thinks back onto his beginnings as CAPTAIN BRITAIN!
description.55: The mighty Warriors Three take on the Big Apple!
description.56: Union Jack battles Baron Blood! Plus, the tragic death of an Invader!
description.57: Kro's army has invaded New York City! Can Sersi protect Margot while Ikaris is rendered unconscious in his battle with Kro?! Meanwhile watching this havoc from afar, Ajack and Daniel Damien also monitor Arishem the Judge at the Inca ruins...
description.58: The Controller cannot be contained! How much more can Iron Man take before he's defeated? Plus: The Blood Brothers are on the loose again! It's a three against one showdown when Iron Man takes on the Controller and the Blood Brothers!
description.60: Thor must fight a dragon and Ulik to get more information to get him closer to finding his missing father Odin.
description.61: Dracula stars in a who's who of fictional classics! Frankenstein's monster, D'Artagnan and more all come for Dracula with one goal - to take him down!
description.62: The X-Men are re-entering Earth's atmosphere aboard a crippled Starcore space shuttle with Jean Grey piloting the ship.
description.63: Return of the Impossible Man! Will the FF's impish foe interfere with the battle between the High Evolutionary and Galactus?
description.75: Guest-starring Nightcrawler of the X-Men! While on a date at Coney Island, Peter and MJ encounter a dangerous sniper. Nightcrawler discovers that an old circus friend was gunned down on Coney Island by the said same sniper. Amongst mistaken identities and miscommunications, Spider-Man and Nightcrawler duke it out to prove their innocence!
description.76: The return of Wonder Man! At a press conference to reveal the new team line-up, the Avengers come face-to-face with a crate holding their long-lost, presumed dead, teammate! But what are the circumstances behind Simon William's mysterious resurrection?
description.77: Cap is on the hunt for the missing Falcon. Little does he know that his friend and ally has been indoctrinated into the cult of the Night People!
description.78: It's a game of Russian roulette, as Black Widow becomes a captive of the Titanium Man! But that's not the only villain emerging from the shadows- Griffin, Rampage, and Crimson Dynamo are also taunting the Champions!
description.79: Mar-Vell and The Supreme Intelligence in a battle of epic proportions!
description.80: The Jester’s gags stop cold, as DD finally confronts the madman behind the murderous mania!
description.88: Witness the origin of the Human Rocket! When young Richard Rider is granted the powers of a Nova Centurion, it becomes his responsibility to use his new abilities to protect the people of Earth!
description.93: Financial Fiasco! Howard and Beverly are having money troubles when Howard finally hits a stroke of luck! When he sees an ad to take on the meanest man in the ring for $10,000, Howard the Duck accepts the challenge of his life!
description.95: While performing a routine 'thug shakedown', Spider-Man is attacked by his own Spider-Mobile! Enter the Tinkerer, the madman villain responsible for the Spider-Mobile's modifications. Will Spider-Man be able to defeat both Tinkerer, and his robot, Toy? And will Aunt May recover from her shocking brush with Doctor Octopus?
description.96: With the team line-up still in flux, Avengers accept an offer only to decline later, or remain in question. Wasp wants to stick around, much to the chagrin of Giant Man. Hawkeye, after accepting an offer, declines to help Two-Gun Kid adjust to the twentieth century. Vision and Scarlet Witch will remain on the team, but only if Hawkeye stays. Hellcat can't seem to make up her mind.
description.97: Captain America and the Falcon are in the grip of the grotesque and strange Night People!

0.text: Nova may be strong, but can he defeat a foe made of pure diamond? And can Richard Rider stand up to the school bully?

1.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

2.text: THE SENTRY STRIKES! Mar-Vell clashes with one of the greatest terrors from his Kree homeworld! Can even the Human Torch help Mar-Vell survive this battle?

3.text: Daredevil is overwhelmed by two pressing cases -- a mad bomber on the loose, and an at-risk runaway teen!

4.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

6.text: Shang-Chi takes on the unstoppable SUMO -- but are mere Kung Fu skills enough?

7.text: Series Finale! Black Panther is challenged by a new villain…Wind Eagle!

8.text: Topaz...transformed into a vicious creature of myth! Meanwhile, Jack Russell may have just gained control of his lycanthropic abilities!

9.text: After being attacked by Stilt-Man with his Z-Ray, Black Goliath, Celia and her nephew find themselves spirited away to the distant planet of Kirgar.

11.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

12.text: Could there be a new costumed Chemistro on the scene? Someone is playing sinister ‘pranks’ on Luke, and Luke is taking the bait. Who is Arch Morton, and what is his connection to original Chemistro, Curtis Carr?

23.text: The Thing teams up with a heroic pioneer, the legendary DOC SAVAGE! Together, they must beat back the menace of the mysterious BLACKSUN!

24.text: Spider-Man, Iron Man, Doctor Strange and Jean DeWolff take part in the trial of Brian and Phillip DeWolff.

25.text: The God of Thunder is joined by his Asgardian comrades to take on Loki and the wicked sorceress, Shamballa!

30.text: Series finale! In their conquest towards glory, Killraven and his Freemen are attacked by alien critters in the Okefenokee Swamp!

31.text: The origin of Viracocha, Incan "god" revealed. What history does Captain Victor Cochran share with the Jaquar Priest? Villac Umu, Jaguar Priest, unleashes a dangerous coup, leaving Skull and his friends caught in battle.

32.text: The Defenders are cast across the globe in this explosive annual! In Washington D.C., Doctor Strange must convince the President that Nebulon’s Mind Control Movement is not in the public’s best interest. Power Man and Valkyrie investigate mysterious deaths in India, while Nighthawk and Red Guardian take on a violent faction in France!

33.text: Vance--in the mind of the Topographical Man--and Nikki--outside of her physical body--do the unthinkable!

37.text: As the ape army marches towards the underground mutant city, Brent is finally reunited with Astronaut George Taylor, but their reunion may not be a happy one, as the mutants have plans of their own!

38.text: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

39.text: New York City has been overrun by a Kung Fu street gang known only as the Golden Tigers. Sounds like the perfect case for mystical crime fighter Iron Fist! Danny Rand makes some inquiries into his father’s shadowy past. Will Rand ever find forgiveness for former mentor Yu-Ti?

40.text: Nova must face the supervillain duo of Powerhouse and the Condor! What are their nefarious plans for the neophyte hero?

41.text: Karen Page makes her long-awaited return in a calamitous crossover with Ghost Rider!

42.text: The Spirit of Vengeance is joined by the Man Without Fear to save Karen Page from the fatal grasp of Death’s Head! New ground is broken in Johnny and Roxanne’s relationship.

43.text: The Hulk's love, Jarella, has been captured and quarantined! And you think you've seen the Hulk mad before…

44.text: Hulk has an untimely brush with an associate of Xemnu's - Diablo!

46.text: Doctor Doom, prisoner of Namorita! Will Namor’s royal cousin prove more merciful than the King of Atlantis? And will Doom finally release Namor from the bonds of Latverian slavery? Find out in this turning point issue of Super-Villain Team-Up!

47.text: The Thing travels from 1976 to 1942, and fights super-powered Nazis alongside the Liberty Legion to reclaim the Canister of Vibranium!

48.text: Cosmic beings threaten to destroy the Universe. Doc suffers a blow by the Ancient One- is Stephen Strange Sorcerer Supreme no longer?

49.text: Valkyrie is reunited with her team, but the period of peace doesn’t last long! Hulk must stop a riot outside a movie theater, while Nighthawk throws money at Jack Norriss to make him go away. (Yes, Nighthawk's that annoyed). Matt Murdock guest stars as Valkyrie’s attorney!

51.text: After a bewitched blunder on his first day of teaching, Daimon Hellstrom makes a clairvoyant connection with Saripha – who reveals she is Wiccan.

52.text: The Thing realizes that the Nazis may still be able to win WWII with their half of the Canister of Vibranium!

53.text: During his Darkmoor battle, Brian Braddock thinks back onto his beginnings as CAPTAIN BRITAIN!

54.text: Doctor Strange joins Spider-Man, Jean DeWolff and Iron Man in a quest to solve the identity of the Wraith!

62.text: The late, great Dave Cockrum introduced the Phoenix to readers with this masterful cover, an appropriately powerful image for one of the X-Men's most celebrated characters.

66.text: The Super-Skrull does his best to demolish Tigra, but Greer has more scratch than expected!

67.text: A strange underground city! Might this be the place that John Brent has been searching for? The mystery of the Silver City only grows deeper when John comes face to face with a group of telepathic humans!

68.text: Shang-Chi, the Master on Kung Fu, partners with Iron Fist to save a damsel!

69.text: Who are the City-Keepers? The House of Agon is at risk of being devoured by a monstrous creation!

70.text: The son of Fu Manchu must now defeat his sister's team of assassins

71.text: Guest-starring Black Panther and the Sub-Mariner! After a serious beat down at the hands of Namor, DD forms an (uneasy) alliance with the King of Atlantis and the King of Wakanda to save a boy from a ransom plot.

74.text: Reprinting Luke Cage, Hero for Hire (1972) #12, available in Unlimited!

79.text: Mar-Vell and The Supreme Intelligence in a battle of epic proportions!

80.text: The Jester’s gags stop cold, as DD finally confronts the madman behind the murderous mania!

82.text: The life and death of Union Jack!  The mysteries of Britain's greatest World War II hero are revealed.  But can even the might of Union Jack and the Invaders stop Baron Blood?

83.text: Doctor Strange and Clea travel to the year 1775 where they board a ship headed to America- with Founding Father Benjamin Franklin in tow!

84.text: The search for Valkyrie begins! Val's behinds bars, (and charged with destruction of property), but the Lady Liberator reaches her breaking point when prison conditions become intolerable. Valkyrie breaks out of solitary…to enter a prison riot!

85.text: Danny makes a shocking discovery about his mother’s demise. How was Iron Fist’s mystic mentor Yu-Ti involved in Heather Rand’s death? Colleen Wing returns to her senses, and teams-up with Iron Fist to take down Angar the Screamer and his brainwashed lackeys!

87.text: “Death’s Dark Dreamer”! Killraven is trapped in the hallucinatory mindscape of a man imprisoned in an “automated museum”.

90.text: Tigra meets Thing for the very first time. And she desperately needs his help.

91.text: Will the power of the Wraith prevail? Spider-Man and Iron Man may have met their match -- meanwhile, Jean discovers that she and Wraith may have something unexpected in common…

92.text: Blade is faced with a moral conundrum when he slays a gang of vampires that have retained their childlike appearance!

98.text: Our unlikely crew of heroes has no choice but to cooperate when taken captive by Supreme Inca, Viracocha. Will Skull and the scientists meet their end in the City of Gold? Ann Reynolds develops a brilliant plot involving pteranodons, while Jeff Turner’s father stages a rescue mission from the outside world. Will this be the twist of fate Skull desperately needs?

99.text: Astronaut John Brent is desperate to find George Taylor, but even with the aid of Ape Scientists Zira and Cornelus, navigating the Planet of the Apes is no simple task.
